          <h3 class="ba-title">Pinterest Native Scheduler — Best free tool for Pinterest marketing</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For businesses with a strong visual product catalog or evergreen content that performs well on Pinterest.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Pinterest's native scheduler lets you queue up to 100 pins scheduled 30 days in advance — standard pins, idea pins, and video pins. Built-in Pinterest analytics show impressions, saves, and clicks. Direct board integration means no third-party connectivity headaches. The obvious limitation: Pinterest only. If Pinterest is a meaningful traffic source for your business (it is for many visual and product-based businesses), this is the simplest free option for managing it.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>100 pins scheduled at once — generous capacity for Pinterest-focused brands</h4><p>Pinterest is an evergreen platform where pins resurface over months. 100 scheduled pins can cover a substantial period.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>All pin types supported: standard, idea, video</h4><p>No pin format restrictions on the free scheduler.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Built-in Pinterest analytics included</h4><p>Impressions, saves, clicks — see what's driving traffic from inside the same tool.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: Pinterest only, 30-day advance scheduling limit</h4><p>Can't manage other platforms here. And 30 days is shorter than Hootsuite's old paid plans allowed — third-party tools often schedule further out.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

